member.remarks:
This method is primarily called when compressing an image. It can be called multiple times 
for a single image if a multiframe image is being compressed. As each frame is compressed, 
an updated offset table is supplied.

member.summary:
Source Item contains Target Content Item.
E.g.: CONTAINER "History" {CONTAINS: TEXT: "mother
had breast cancer"; CONTAINS IMAGE 36}

Used to qualify or describe the Concept Name of the
Source Content item, such as to create a post-coordinated
description of a concept, or to further describe a concept.
E.g. CODE "Chest X-Ray" {HAS CONCEPT MOD: CODE
"View = PA and Lateral"}
E.g. CODE "Breast" {HAS CONCEPT MOD: TEXT "French
Translation" = "Sein"}
E.g. CODE "2VCXRPALAT" {HAS CONCEPT MOD: TEXT
"Further Explanation" = "Chest X-Ray, Two Views, Posteroanterior
and Lateral"}

member.exception:
The name argument was null 
            or was an empty string; or contexts was null or had a length of zero;
            or  consisted of more than 129 characters.

The name argument was null or 
            was an empty string; or contexts was null or had a length of zero;
            or the name consisted of more than 129 characters.

